  "prompt": "How do you politely turn down someone who wants to \"grab coffee sometime\"?",
  "response": "Turning down a coffee invitation politely can be done with kindness and clarity. Here are a few responses you could consider:\n\n1. **Be Direct but Gentle**: \n   - \"Thank you so much for the invite! I appreciate it, but I'm not able to meet for coffee right now.\"\n\n2. **Express Gratitude**:\n   - \"Thanks for asking! It's really nice of you, but I\u2019m currently busy with other commitments.\"\n\n3. **Suggest Alternatives**:\n   - \"I really appreciate the offer! However, I\u2019m not able to meet up right now. Let\u2019s keep in touch through messages instead.\"\n\n4. **Keep it Vague**:\n   - \"Thanks for the invite, but I\u2019m in a really busy season of my life at the moment.\"\n\n5. **Be Honest (if appropriate)**:\n   - \"I genuinely appreciate your invitation, but I\u2019m focusing on some personal matters and need to decline.\"\n\nRemember to maintain a friendly tone to ensure the message is received positively.",
